replyContent: It happens when you fill your memory. The OS closes the app because it treats it as unnecessarily small. The only way to keep it from happening is to force close all other apps you don't need for playing the game. There's a memory management tutorial in the HELP section

This is perhaps the best app available for Golf Clash players (Android only) for wind adjustment. The intuitive design with a userfriendly interface and unobstructive widgets, make it a pleasure to use. Since it has been designed by top GC players (Zack and Ian), it provides you with the required information in the right sized window without distracting you from the game. Now bear in mind that it does take a few rounds of play to get used to as you need to multitask; however, Zack has provided tutorial lessons on his Facebook page to take you through every step. The only feedback I can provide to the developers is to allow customization of the grid like color change or increase/decrease in its opaqueness as the current bright red color is sometimes distracting. So, great job and thanks for making this app that takes all the mundane work of wind calcs out of the game and allows you to be more strategic and accurate in your gameplay. Hope you will continue to update this app with suggested changes and enhancements.
